Aneka Tambang, Indika, Telekomunikasi: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-03-02T01:46:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/aneka-tambang-indika-telekomunikasi-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 1.2 percent to 3,512.62.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures gained 2.7 percent to
$99.63 a barrel in  New York  yesterday, the highest settlement
since September 2008. The contract rose 0.7 percent to $100.34 a
barrel in after-hours trading as of 8:04 a.m. Jakarta time.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),  Indonesia â€™s
biggest listed oil company, advanced 0.9 percent to 2,950 rupiah.
PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second biggest, advanced
3.7 percent to 112 rupiah.  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ): The second-biggest nickel
producer and Eramet SA plan to build a nickel smelter in North
Maluku province with a capacity of 27,000 tons a year at an
estimated cost of $3 billion to $4 billion, Kontan reported,
citing Aneka President Director Alwin Syah Loebis. Aneka gained
3.4 percent to 2,275 rupiah.  PT Indika Energy (INDY IJ): The coal producer may acquire a
51 percent stake in PT Mitrabahtera Segara Sejati for as much as
1.82 trillion rupiah ($207 million) as part of an option
agreement,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing Deddy Happy Handi,
a director at Mitrabahtera, an Indonesian coal transport company.
Indika advanced 1.3 percent to 3,850 rupiah.  PT Telekomunikasi Indonesia (TLKM IJ): The biggest
telephone company may spend 151 trillion rupiah on  capital
expenditures  from this year until 2015, Investor Daily Indonesia
reported, citing Eddy Kurnia, a spokesman at the company said.
Telekomunikasi climbed 0.7 percent to 7,500 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
